In England, in the seven days to 21 November, there were 244,956 new confirmed cases (433.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 November, there were 222,862 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 10% (22,094 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 November is 8,538,517 (15,099 cases per 100,000 population).
